# Welcome!

#### Welcome! Code.org’s Equity in Computer Science professional learning experience is designed to help educators reflect and take action to make their classrooms **diverse**, **accessible**, and **inclusive** for all students.

## Course Overview

### **What's included in this course?**

<div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 20px; margin-top: 20px;">
    <div style="background-color: #ffffff; box-shadow: 0px 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3); padding: 15px; border-radius: 10px; width: 45%;">
    <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center;">
            <img src="https://images.code.org/7f9f49bb33623ac2d0aefbdf927f49ec-image-1732314462425.png" alt="A icon of a person holding up a lightbulb as if they have an idea." style="width: 80px; height: 80px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
        </div>
    <p style="color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px"><b>Module 1:</b> Understanding Equity in Computer Science (📍 You are here!)</p>
<p style="color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px">The first module in this course will provide you with a conceptual foundation for equity. You'll reflect on your own personal journeys and orient yourself toward equity in the classroom.</p>
<br>
<p style="color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px"><b>Module 1 is made up of three lessons:</b></p>

* #### What is Equity in CS?
* #### Looking at Data
* #### Reflecting on Personal Experiences
    </div>

<div style="background-color: #ffffff; box-shadow: 0px 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3); padding: 15px; border-radius: 10px; width: 45%;">
    <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center;">
            <img src="https://images.code.org/2791d97403ebd52030b55642aa6e8d1d-image-1732314232992.png" alt="An icon of a school house." style="width: 80px; height: 80px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
    </div>
        <p style="color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px"><b>Module 2:</b> Strategies to Promote Equity in Computer Science</p>
        <p style="color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px">The second module in this course will get concrete about strategies you can use with your students. This unit is oriented toward resources to bridge professional learning to the classroom.</p>

<p style="color: black; line-height: 1.25; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px"><b>Module 2 is made up of four lessons:</b></p>

* #### Expanding Access to Computer Science
* #### Cultivating an Inclusive Classroom Culture
* #### Bias and Stereotype Threat
* #### Equity in Code.org’s Curriculum
</div>
</div>

<div style="display: flex; align-items: left; border: 1px solid black; border-radius: 20px 20px 20px 20px; padding: 20px 10px 10px 10px; margin: 20px 0px 20px 0px">

